
## Encrypt Example: TrustPay

> TrustPay example: 

```xml
<Encrypt>
  <shopLogin>90000001</shopLogin>
  <uicCode>242</uicCode><!-- Euro -->
  <amount>0.10</amount>
  <shopTransactionId>MYSHOP_001</shopTransactionId>
  <paymentTypes>
    <paymentType>TRUSTPAY</paymentType>
  </paymentTypes>
  <OrderDetails>
    <CutomerDetail>
      <PrimaryEmail>indiana@jones.com</PrimaryEmail>
    </CustomerDetail>
    <BillingAddress>
      <CountryCode>CZ</CountryCode>
    </BillingAddress>
  </OrderDetails>
</Encrypt>
```

You must use `TRUSTPAY` as `paymentType`.

TrustPay requires some mandatory parameters: 

| Field | Description | 
| ----- | ----------- | 
| `PrimaryEmail` | The user email address, contained in `OrderDetails.CustomerDetail` |
| `CountryCode` | In `OrderDetails.BillingAddress`, there must be one of the allowed Country codes: `['CZ', 'EE', 'HU', 'LT', 'LV', 'SI', 'SK', 'TR']`. | 

Click on [`OrderDetails`](#orderdetails) to know more about its structure.

